observations.recommendation:
We recommend that management submit a formal letter explaining the following:

Reason why the Office of the Mayor, instead of the Office of the Municipal Engineering, is servicing the rentals of heavy equipment;

Fuel expenses of rented heavy equipment by private individuals are charged to the LGU funds;

Rental payments are received only after services were rendered;

Rental rates were beyond the prescribed rates stated in the Local Revenue Code.

We recommend that management submit a formal letter explaining the following:
Reason why the Office of the Mayor, instead of the Office of the Municipal Engineering, is servicing the rentals of heavy equipment;
Fuel expenses of rented heavy equipment by private individuals are charged to the LGU funds;
Rental payments are received only after services were rendered;
Rental rates were beyond the prescribed rates stated in the Local Revenue Code.
Further, we recommend that management propose to the SB the upgrading of the Local Revenue Code relative to the rental rates of heavy equipment to be at par with the prevailing rates. Finally, strict compliance to the provisions of the local revenue code must be observed at all times in the case of rentals of heavy equipment and facilities of the LGU.
